IF THERE’S one thing Blessing ‘Bled’ Chimanga knows how to do well, it is play the drums. From just a small boy beating tins in his mother’s backyard to becoming one of Zimbabwe’s hottest drumming and marimba exports, Bled has cemented his reputation as a musical force to be reckoned with. With his insatiable lust for life, abundant passion and inherent musical talent, Bled was always tipped for the top. He was a natural school leader, and nurtured his musical talents throughout his youth, becoming a session drummer after leaving school. He went on to record more than 50 albums as a session drummer for various artists. But it was in 2011 at just 21 years old that Bled’s life took a different turn — one that would open up doors he’d only ever dreamt about. He met Italian musician Max Covini, and the two started the Zimbabwe and Italy music collaboration project Zimboita. “We toured Africa and Europe, and recorded an album together. This led to my big international break and was soon I was facilitating African music workshops and performing at concerts abroad,” Bled recalls. On the fast-track to fame, his own original albums soon followed. Bled released his first solo album, Dreams, featuring the hit song Maruva Enyika in 2015, and followed this up three years later with TOSE. This second album was equally favourably received, resulting in a string of performances in India and Indonesia.        This included performing for the Prince of Chennai in India. Bled has performed in 20 countries over the past 10 years. Today he tours nine months of the year, doing what he loves best…and always with a smile! Over the years he has also been selected to represent Zimbabwe in a number of international exchange programmes, including ONEBEAT in the USA. This particular programme featured 36 artists from around the world, with Bled flying the flag for Zimbabwe. Throughout this time Bled never forgot his roots, and consistently sought ways to give back to his country using music as a vehicle to bring about positive change. As such he sits on the boards of various music organisations; is part of the planning committee of the National Institute of Allied Arts, an annual music festival for Zimbabwean schools; and since 2018 has been the musical director of the prestigious Harare International Festival of the Arts (HIFA), one of the biggest local arts festivals. Bled founded the first-ever annual marimba camp for Zimbabwean school children, and developed Celebrate Africa, a purely African music competition and talent search to celebrate the youth playing African instruments. This initiative was made possible with the support of MultiChoice Zimbabwe, for which Bled says he remains incredibly grateful. “MultiChoice Zimbabwe helped me further my vision of empowering our children. “MultiChoice has also supported my Big Smile outreach project, an initiative I started in 2008 to help local children’s homes. “In June and December every year I arrange for food, clothes and blanket donations for children’s homes. “In the beginning I used my personal savings for this, but it has grown into a group of young people working together to donate funds to cover the basic needs of at least two homes per year,” Bled explains, adding that he has built a genuine friendship with MultiChoice over the years, and today considers himself a self-appointed DStv ambassador! One of the most rewarding aspects of his life outside his partnership with MultiChoice Zimbabwe is coaching marimba in schools. Bled coached a group of youth who were named the best in Zimbabwe and later, the best in Africa. “This band has now toured Argentina, the USA and South Africa, and recorded more than 2 million Facebook views of one of its videos!” Bled enthuses. “I am so grateful to have been given this opportunity to nurture this talent and grow Zimbabwean culture in this generation. “Marimba is our national instrument, and this success demonstrates that we are keeping our heritage alive. What could be better than that?” Sponsored Links                                              Classifieds.co.zw                                                                                                                      Property, Houses                                                                                                                                                      Building Supplies                                                                                                                                                      Electronics                                                                                                                                                      Cars                                                                                                                                                      Home & Garden                                                                                                                                                      Commercial Supplies                                                                                                                                                      Services                                                                                                                                                      Health & Beauty                                                                                                                                                      Dating                                                                                                                                                      Jobs                                                                                                                                         Webdev                                                                                                                                          Domains                           